<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,528,1018]" box="[151,1349,528,554]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
This genus was originally comprised of 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1851" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1851" box="[621,920,528,554]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ctenostylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufum">
<emphasis box="[621,725,528,553]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">C. rufum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart" box="[732,920,528,554]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Macquart, P. J. M. (1851) Dipteres exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. Suite du 4 e. suplement. Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences de Agriculture et des Arts de Lille, 1850, 134 - 294." type="journal article" year="1851">
Macquart, 
<number box="[859,920,528,554]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="1851.0">1851</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from one male specimen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,528,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Soon after the original description the type-specimen was studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bigot" box="[1059,1214,566,592]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="Bigot, J. M. F. (1882) Dipteres nouveaux ou peu connus. 19 e partie. XXIX. Genres Roeselia, Actia, Melia, Phytomyptera et tribu des Anthomyzidae (Schiner, Rondani, Meade). XXX. Genre Ctenostylum. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 6 (2), 5 - 22." type="journal article" year="1882">
Bigot (
<number box="[1145,1206,566,592]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="1882.0">1882</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
who rectified the original description. 
<bibRefCitation author="McAlpine" box="[393,596,605,631]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="McAlpine, D. K. (1989) The taxonomic position of the Ctenostylidae (= Lochmostyliinae) (Diptera: Schizophora). Memorias do Instituto Oswaldo Cruz, 84 (Suppl. 4), 365 - 371." type="journal article" year="1989">
McAlpine (
<number box="[527,588,605,631]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported that the 
<typeStatus box="[801,851,605,631]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[889,1112,605,630]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ctenostylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufum">
<emphasis box="[889,1112,605,630]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Ctenostylum rufum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was lost and he described a male from 
<collectingCountry box="[287,421,644,670]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
but did not give a name to it. He did not evaluate variation between the two male specimens because Macquart’s description was not very detailed, the illustrations were innacurate and a series of specimens was not available.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,528,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Looking for ctenostylid specimens in the Amazon Basin we found one 
<taxonomicName box="[1047,1195,760,785]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ctenostylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1047,1195,760,785]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Ctenostylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen housed at 
<collectionCode box="[151,233,798,824]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/90vz-swjg" name="Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">MPEG</collectionCode>
. It was collected in Serra Norte, Carajás, Southeastern Pará state, and it appeard to be different from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ctenostylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">C. rufum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to Macquart’s original description and Bigot’s (
<number box="[930,993,837,863]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="1882.0">1882</number>
) rectification, and different from the undescribed male from 
<collectingCountry box="[437,569,876,902]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="McAlpine" box="[585,782,876,902]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="McAlpine, D. K. (1989) The taxonomic position of the Ctenostylidae (= Lochmostyliinae) (Diptera: Schizophora). Memorias do Instituto Oswaldo Cruz, 84 (Suppl. 4), 365 - 371." type="journal article" year="1989">
McAlpine 
<number box="[717,782,876,902]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The two previously-known specimens are males and here we describe the first female of this genus. The arista of the female is very complex, with dendritic branching (
<figureCitation box="[286,359,953,979]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,272,1809,1833]" captionTargetBox="[265,1322,594,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[264,1323,589,1784]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 1, head, frontal view; 2, head, lateral view; 3, head, dorsal view; 4, antennae; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, thorax, lateral view; 7, wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186178/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[342,359,953,979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), identical to females of other ctenostylid genera. but female tergite and sternite 
<number box="[1323,1338,953,979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="7.0">7</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[1355,1426,953,979]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[269,1322,544,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[264,1323,542,1548]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 12. Ctenostylum fuscomaculatum, n. sp., holotype. 8, abdomen, dorsal view; 9, abdomen, ventral view; 10, distal abdominal segment, lateral view; 11, cerci, ventral view; 12, internal egg." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/186179/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[1411,1426,953,979]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) are not fused, as is found in the remainder of the family(
<bibRefCitation author="McAlpine" box="[810,1000,992,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="68" refString="McAlpine, D. K. (1989) The taxonomic position of the Ctenostylidae (= Lochmostyliinae) (Diptera: Schizophora). Memorias do Instituto Oswaldo Cruz, 84 (Suppl. 4), 365 - 371." type="journal article" year="1989">
McAlpine 
<number box="[937,1000,992,1018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
